description: For sale: $2,300,000. Beautiful custom home built and designed by Denali Custom Homes in 2016.  Perfectly positioned on a 7.09 acre lot to maximize views of Lk Minnetonka. Quiet and private with 2 apple orchards, 60'x40' outbuilding prepped for insulation, custom designed and heated chicken coop, mature trees and nature surrounds. Home includes grand spaces, large windows, bedrooms with lake views, screen porch 48x10. Seller's own adjoining buildable 2.57 acre lot (not included/SEE SUPPLIEMENTS FOR MAP OVERVIEW) which is listed on lots/land.  Could be sold separately or with home.

For sale: $789,900. Freshly updated home on Lake Independence.   Sprawling floor plan includes vaulted great room, hardwood floors and stone fireplace. Upper level includes a large master suite with luxury bath, two additional bedrooms and a full family bath.  Lower family room is a great space to gather and shares the level with an additional bedroom, bath and large storage area.  Peaceful setting surrounded by nature, long westerly views and level lawn leading to the lake and new boat house.  Extra bonus  - detached shop/guest house structure with 750 square feet of additional living space, Perfect set up for an in-law apartment or a home office.  Orono Schools.

For sale: $245,000. Welcome Home! This amazing home is move in ready and has so many updates for you to enjoy! Whether you are an investor looking for a ready to go rental or just for you and your family, this home checks all the boxes. You have 3 bedrooms on one level, all new appliances in the kitchen, a huge garage for all your toys and projects and so much more. With everything done you will actually have time to enjoy your weekends and summer nights grilling on the back deck! You are also located in the Orono School District. And the home comes with the adjoining .1307 acre lot for even more potential to build equity in the future. Quick close is possible and it is easy to show.

Zestimate® Home Value: $252,980. Charming and well maintained home in the heart of Maple Plain! You're welcomed into the home by gleaming hardwood floors, an abundance of natural light, and an invting floorplan. The main level features a generously sized living room, three bedrooms, an updated kitchen & full bathroom, and formal dining room. Make your way downstairs where you'll find a flexible room that can be used as a bedroom, office, or family room. A half bathroom and storage area will also be found in the lower level.The home is situated on a double lot with a detached 3 car garage! The one car tuckunder stall can be used as storage or a workspace. With some finishing touches you can make this home yours! Located conveniently near highway 12, making your commute to and from the city a breeze.

The master's wing has a sitting area with fireplace, large walk-in closet, spa-like master bathroom w/ heated limestone floors and steam shower, and exercise room with laundry. Enjoy the seclusion of the property on your large wrap around deck complete w/ wood burning fireplace and propane grill. Plenty of room for all of your toys and hobbies in the detached garage w/ shop. Open enrollment available 4 schools!

Open floor plan is wonderful for entertaining and easily flows from kitchen island to dining room to great room.  Huge prep pantry to store all your dry goods and offers a place to keep small appliances from cluttering your kitchen counter-tops.  Large mud room has closet for all the sports gear and study is tucked behind the kitchen for a quiet place to work.  
Upstairs there is a beautiful owners suite with huge walk in closet, a junior suite, 2 more bedrooms, bath, convenient laundry room, and loft area.
Unfinished lower level is just waiting for your ideas and personal touch, but offers potential for media room, walk out game room, 5th bedroom, bath and gallery.
Gargage is 20x22 plus 3rd stall at 12x22.   All information, amenities, room sizes and square footage are for proposed home and not guaranteed.

Recently sold: $300,000. Beautiful home in Orono school district, overlooking Rainbow Park!  Bright and inviting with updates everywhere - white cabinetry throughout, granite countertops, vinyl windows, oversized mudroom, large multi-level deck, great yard with 8 raised flower beds on south side, storage shed.  New AC in '17, water heater in '18, most everything else updated by previous owner in '15.  Run right through the backyard to Rainbow Park - playground, ice rink with warming house, tennis, pickle ball and basketball courts, baseball/t-ball diamonds, paved 1/2 mile walking trail, community garden, yearly neighborhood fun run and lots of pick up sports games!

description:
Recently sold: $979,500. Be swimming this summer! This remarkable rambler on 5.5 acres has it all, and in the Orono School District. Extraordinary finishing details and mechanical upgrades. ALL floors on both levels feature in-floor radiant heat...including the garage.. This super-comfortable home also boasts a huge center-isle kitchen, 2 main floor bedroom suites and striking vaulted entry parlor. The lower level has a large bedroom, easily divided into two bedrooms if desired. This bedroom features a private bath with 3-sink vanity and huge closet. You will also find an amusement room and huge media room with home-theater. There is very ample storage and a walkout to the secluded yard.
The newer in-ground pool has full patio as well as a pool house with a gas fireplace. Enjoy the fire-pit and pool in total privacy .
Very flexible closing. Near Baker Park and Golf and Lake Independence Beach. This is a Boyer-Built, DeNovo Designed custom home. Only one stop to Downtown Mpls via 12/394.

Recently sold: $369,000. Spotless home on a manicured treed yard in award winning Orono school district.  Open main floor with hard surface floors and expanses of sun-filled windows. Spacious game room and family room with fireplace.  4 bedrooms, 2 baths inclusive of a private master bath.  Spacious south-facing deck overlooking a private landscaped, croquet-ready rear yard.   block to North Baker Regional Park and trails, and steps to Lake Independence.  Numerous updates and fresh decor inside and out.

Recently sold: $125,000. This home is a Real Estate Owned (REO)/Post Foreclosure. Once a lender has foreclosed on a property it is soon put up for public auction. If bids fall short of the asking price the bank will buy back the home and attempt to sell it on the open market. However, lenders are not real estate agents, meaning that they will often accept offers significantly below market value!

Foyer
Welcoming you into the home is a beautiful foyer with a leaded glass door, a large closet, and hardwood floors.

Kitchen

Laundry
